1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,503
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,586 --> 00:00:08,466
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,635
♪ <i>Fix it</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,719 --> 00:00:12,804
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:16,224
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,850 --> 00:00:17,976
- [Audrey] <i>I need your help.</i>
- [upbeat music playing]

7
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:19,686
<i>Janine ran away!</i>

8
00:00:19,769 --> 00:00:20,770
I'm chasing someone.

9
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:22,105
This person I'm after is dangerous.

10
00:00:22,188 --> 00:00:23,022
I need to get there--

11
00:00:23,106 --> 00:00:24,524
Atoy, Janine is our child!

12
00:00:24,607 --> 00:00:25,483
PREVIOUSLY

13
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:26,568
[Aldrin] <i>You're still hiding from me.</i>

14
00:00:26,651 --> 00:00:28,403
[Aldrin] You think I won't find you?

15
00:00:28,486 --> 00:00:29,863
Come here.

16
00:00:29,946 --> 00:00:31,031
[Paldo] <i>Eh, what…</i>

17
00:00:31,114 --> 00:00:32,073
<i>What happened to you? Ba--</i>

18
00:00:32,157 --> 00:00:32,991
[Emerson] <i>Because we were…</i>

19
00:00:33,074 --> 00:00:34,868
<i>chasing a criminal.</i>

20
00:00:34,951 --> 00:00:36,953
I got hit by… by this kid!

21
00:00:37,037 --> 00:00:39,873
[Emerson] <i>Eh, this child turned out to be…</i>

22
00:00:39,956 --> 00:00:41,499
- <i>the child of Atoy's fling who…</i>
- Janine?

23
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:43,501
<i>looks like Mama Mary.</i>

24
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:44,878
You mean Atoy is here?

25
00:00:44,961 --> 00:00:46,337
You saw we were playing.

26
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:48,173
- [Aldrin] <i>You won't stop bothering me?!</i>
- [Atoy] <i>Relax, bro!</i>

27
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:49,799
You're just tiring yourself out!

28
00:00:50,425 --> 00:00:51,634
[grunting]

29
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:54,345
[Audrey] <i>Thank you, Atoy.</i>

30
00:00:54,429 --> 00:00:56,181
[Atoy] <i>If I can help other people,</i>

31
00:00:56,264 --> 00:00:57,682
<i>of course, I can help my own daughter.</i>

32
00:00:57,766 --> 00:00:59,726
[Mongki] <i>They said some man interfered,</i>

33
00:00:59,809 --> 00:01:01,770
- <i>who helped the child.</i>
- [Red] <i>Who?</i>

34
00:01:01,853 --> 00:01:04,522
Who is this man ruining my plan?
Find that out!

35
00:01:04,606 --> 00:01:07,025
[Ibyang] So, you want to find
Sister Norma,

36
00:01:07,108 --> 00:01:10,904
to ask her who my real parents are?

37
00:01:10,987 --> 00:01:13,948
Yes, so we'll finally know.

38
00:01:14,032 --> 00:01:16,659
That's not needed anymore.

39
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:18,703
I already have Tatoy!

40
00:01:19,287 --> 00:01:23,124
He doesn't have a child,
so I'll be his child.

41
00:01:28,213 --> 00:01:29,964
- [music fades]
- [grunts]

42
00:01:30,048 --> 00:01:31,049
[Emerson] There.

43
00:01:31,132 --> 00:01:32,175
There.

44
00:01:33,092 --> 00:01:34,135
[Emerson grunts]

45
00:01:34,219 --> 00:01:36,304
- There, there, there.
- Yes, okay.

46
00:01:36,387 --> 00:01:40,016
- There, there.
- Ouch, ouch.

47
00:01:40,099 --> 00:01:42,143
What really happened to you, brother?

48
00:01:42,227 --> 00:01:43,645
[in Visayan] Bro, you're unbelievable!

49
00:01:43,728 --> 00:01:44,604
Ah.

50
00:01:44,687 --> 00:01:46,523
[in Visayan] Don't be noisy, Netchai!

51
00:01:47,148 --> 00:01:50,193
It's nothing. I just had a mishap because…

52
00:01:50,276 --> 00:01:52,570
I helped Atoy in his mission.

53
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:54,781
- You?! Ah--
- [quirky sting]

54
00:01:54,864 --> 00:01:56,866
- I mean… you? [smirks]
- You're being mean.

55
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,952
[Emerson] You don't believe me at all.

56
00:01:59,035 --> 00:02:01,329
For your information, if not for me…

57
00:02:01,412 --> 00:02:03,498
Atoy probably wouldn't
have found his child.

58
00:02:03,581 --> 00:02:04,666
[gasps]

59
00:02:05,166 --> 00:02:07,252
Ibyang is his daughter!

60
00:02:07,335 --> 00:02:08,336
- Right?
- Psst, hey.

61
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:10,588
Keep your voice down.

62
00:02:11,172 --> 00:02:13,424
[Emerson] Not Ibyang, another child.

63
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:15,176
That's a secret.

64
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:17,053
Okay, fine. I'll tell you the truth.

65
00:02:17,762 --> 00:02:20,348
Yes, Atoy really has a child.

66
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:22,851
Who did he get pregnant this time?!

67
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:23,852
[deep breath]

68
00:02:23,935 --> 00:02:28,606
The one who looks like Mama Mary,
at Ibyang's school.

69
00:02:29,357 --> 00:02:32,277
His… summer fling.

70
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:35,697
The… The beauty--

71
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:38,575
[sauve theme music playing]

72
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:39,993
[motorcycle revving]

73
00:02:40,076 --> 00:02:41,452
[sewing machine whirring]

74
00:02:41,536 --> 00:02:42,412
[scratches]

75
00:02:42,495 --> 00:02:43,371
[snipping]

76
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:48,293
[sewing machine clacking]

77
00:02:49,168 --> 00:02:51,671
[gunshots blasting]

78
00:02:51,754 --> 00:02:53,047
[music intensifies]

79
00:02:53,131 --> 00:02:53,965
[clicking]

80
00:02:54,048 --> 00:02:56,050
[snipping]

81
00:02:58,386 --> 00:03:00,763
[electronic blipping]

82
00:03:03,308 --> 00:03:05,018
- [music fades]
- [siren blaring]

83
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:09,522
[door chimes clinking]

84
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:12,775
Oh! Jesus Mary Joseph!

85
00:03:12,859 --> 00:03:15,069
What are you doing there?

86
00:03:15,987 --> 00:03:18,031
You're not asleep yet, huh?

87
00:03:18,114 --> 00:03:19,782
Is there a problem?

88
00:03:23,369 --> 00:03:24,203
Godmother…

89
00:03:26,497 --> 00:03:28,541
You know Audrey, right?

90
00:03:31,085 --> 00:03:34,213
And you know she has a daughter, Janine.

91
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:36,466
Oh?

92
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:39,552
I found out yesterday…

93
00:03:40,053 --> 00:03:44,641
[pensive music playing]

94
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:46,351
…that Janine is my child.

95
00:03:47,101 --> 00:03:48,228
Really?

96
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:49,520
Oh?

97
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:53,191
Why, don't you want that?

98
00:03:53,274 --> 00:03:55,151
No. Of course, of course…

99
00:03:55,235 --> 00:03:57,028
Of course I want that.

100
00:03:57,528 --> 00:03:58,488
Er, there's no…

101
00:03:58,571 --> 00:04:00,114
If it's true, right?

102
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:02,450
But for me…

103
00:04:03,534 --> 00:04:04,619
I was living a quiet life,

104
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:08,039
then suddenly someone tells me
I have a child.

105
00:04:08,122 --> 00:04:10,458
Why-- Why did she just tell me now, right?

106
00:04:10,541 --> 00:04:12,585
Oh, well, you already have
a daughter, right?

107
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:13,711
Ibyang!

108
00:04:13,795 --> 00:04:15,171
She may not have come from you,

109
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:17,507
not like Janine, but…

110
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,133
that's the only difference!

111
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:21,302
Uh, of course…

112
00:04:21,386 --> 00:04:22,387
[clicks tongue]

113
00:04:22,887 --> 00:04:24,472
[inhales]

114
00:04:24,555 --> 00:04:25,848
Ibyang is different.

115
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:27,058
[Atoy inhales]

116
00:04:27,141 --> 00:04:30,270
But of course, with Ibyang, I was ready,

117
00:04:30,353 --> 00:04:32,647
because it was my decision to adopt her.

118
00:04:33,815 --> 00:04:35,483
But Janine…

119
00:04:36,985 --> 00:04:37,986
No.

120
00:04:39,946 --> 00:04:44,867
Imagine, I don't even know how to be
a father to one child.

121
00:04:44,951 --> 00:04:46,619
How about for two?

122
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:47,578
[sighs]

123
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:49,455
Oh, so what will you do?

124
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:52,292
You won't accept Janine as your child?

125
00:04:52,375 --> 00:04:55,128
No, Godmother. Of course I'll accept her.

126
00:04:55,211 --> 00:04:58,673
Of course I won't turn my back
on my responsibility to her.

127
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:01,718
But…

128
00:05:03,386 --> 00:05:07,765
But maybe she should know
that I'm her father.

129
00:05:07,849 --> 00:05:08,975
Right, Mom?

130
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:12,562
Because I just found out yesterday.

131
00:05:12,645 --> 00:05:14,439
She doesn't even know yet.

132
00:05:14,522 --> 00:05:17,191
[sighs] It's really hard
to break the news to a child.

133
00:05:17,275 --> 00:05:20,278
Especially if she isn't that nice.

134
00:05:20,361 --> 00:05:23,531
I don't even know how she was raised.

135
00:05:23,614 --> 00:05:25,658
Why does she act that way?

136
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:29,829
That's why I think it's better
if I really act as her father.

137
00:05:29,912 --> 00:05:35,668
So, at least I can help Audrey teach
the right manners to the child.

138
00:05:36,669 --> 00:05:37,545
[clicks tongue]

139
00:05:37,628 --> 00:05:39,839
That's the right decision.

140
00:05:39,922 --> 00:05:43,134
It's really important
for a child growing up

141
00:05:43,217 --> 00:05:45,470
to have both parents.

142
00:05:45,553 --> 00:05:48,347
Don't forget about Ibyang, okay?

143
00:05:48,431 --> 00:05:50,933
All right, settle
your situation with Janine.

144
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:54,604
Of course, Ibyang already
considers you her father.

145
00:05:54,687 --> 00:05:58,066
But you should also prepare
for how she'll feel.

146
00:05:58,149 --> 00:06:01,027
[melodramatic music playing]

147
00:06:01,110 --> 00:06:02,278
Yes.

148
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:06,949
Yes, Mom.

149
00:06:07,033 --> 00:06:09,744
Get some rest if you can.

150
00:06:09,827 --> 00:06:11,454
You haven't slept yet.

151
00:06:42,235 --> 00:06:44,612
[music fades]

152
00:06:44,695 --> 00:06:47,573
[Martina, in English]
Welcome home, baby girl!

153
00:06:47,657 --> 00:06:48,533
[Martina sighs]

154
00:06:49,534 --> 00:06:51,035
Good thing you're safe.

155
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:52,578
You made us worry.

156
00:06:53,204 --> 00:06:55,331
I'll just go to my room.

157
00:06:55,414 --> 00:06:56,457
Oh, okay, dear.

158
00:06:56,541 --> 00:06:58,543
Please go with her.

159
00:06:58,626 --> 00:06:59,752
[in English]Thank you.

160
00:07:04,799 --> 00:07:06,300
[pensive music playing]

161
00:07:06,384 --> 00:07:07,343
Excuse me, sir.

162
00:07:08,344 --> 00:07:09,554
Good morning!

163
00:07:09,637 --> 00:07:10,638
- [Dmitri] Good morning.
- I am Sergeant Lim.

164
00:07:10,721 --> 00:07:13,641
[Lim] We spoke with Ma'am Audrey
last night at the hospital.

165
00:07:13,724 --> 00:07:16,894
I just want to give an update
about what happened last night.

166
00:07:16,978 --> 00:07:19,480
We already caught the one
who wanted to kidnap the child.

167
00:07:19,564 --> 00:07:20,606
Aldrin Galang.

168
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:24,735
We suspect he's a member
of a human trafficking syndicate.

169
00:07:24,819 --> 00:07:26,571
Was he acting alone?

170
00:07:26,654 --> 00:07:28,281
Or did he have accomplices?

171
00:07:28,364 --> 00:07:29,699
[Lim] I'm sure of it.

172
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:31,742
But the suspect isn't talking.

173
00:07:32,326 --> 00:07:33,369
Thank you, Sergeant.

174
00:07:33,453 --> 00:07:34,537
Okay.

175
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:36,664
[music fades]

176
00:07:36,747 --> 00:07:39,625
Oh my God! Wow!
The world is really getting worse.

177
00:07:39,709 --> 00:07:40,918
These syndicates are multiplying.

178
00:07:41,002 --> 00:07:43,045
[in English] I mean,
it seems like they're everywhere.

179
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:44,881
[in English]My thoughts exactly.

180
00:07:44,964 --> 00:07:47,592
[in English] I mean, we don't even
have to look far, right?

181
00:07:47,675 --> 00:07:49,218
Even here at home, there is.

182
00:07:49,302 --> 00:07:50,720
[dramatic sting]

183
00:07:51,304 --> 00:07:53,055
[in English] That was a long time ago.

184
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:55,349
I've changed, dear.

185
00:07:55,975 --> 00:07:59,228
You still suspect me until now?

186
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:01,272
[in English] Ah, I know.
I'm-- I'm sorry, Dad.

187
00:08:01,355 --> 00:08:03,149
I didn't mean to.

188
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:09,280
I just can't believe that…
my child almost got taken.

189
00:08:09,363 --> 00:08:11,365
You know, Audrey,

190
00:08:11,449 --> 00:08:14,535
next time, you should be a little bit
more patient with the kid.

191
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:17,455
I mean, we're lucky that

192
00:08:17,538 --> 00:08:18,998
we got her back.

193
00:08:19,081 --> 00:08:21,834
If not, her organs might have
ended up all over the place, right?

194
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:25,588
I mean, we did bring her to you whole,
with no missing body parts, right?

195
00:08:25,671 --> 00:08:26,964
Martina!

196
00:08:27,048 --> 00:08:31,135
[tense music playing]

197
00:08:35,139 --> 00:08:37,892
- [music concludes]
- Dear, I cooked this.

198
00:08:38,392 --> 00:08:41,646
You should eat first.
Enough with that gadget!

199
00:08:42,313 --> 00:08:43,564
Come on.

200
00:08:46,442 --> 00:08:48,236
I don't like that food.

201
00:08:51,072 --> 00:08:52,865
Just try it first.

202
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:56,327
I said I don't like it.

203
00:08:56,827 --> 00:08:58,454
I'll just go to my room.

204
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:04,210
[somber music playing]

205
00:09:06,170 --> 00:09:08,548
My child's still holding
a grudge against me.

206
00:09:09,507 --> 00:09:11,300
Looks like it, Auntie.

207
00:09:11,384 --> 00:09:12,552
Well, she's still a kid.

208
00:09:13,052 --> 00:09:15,763
I'm sure when you were young,
you were like that too.

209
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:18,474
Well, yes.

210
00:09:19,517 --> 00:09:23,938
But you know what?
When I was young, I wasn't like Janine.

211
00:09:24,438 --> 00:09:29,986
I remember, when Dad approached me
and showed affection…

212
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:31,737
I'd be okay.

213
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:33,781
So, you were a daddy's girl.

214
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:37,577
Maybe that's what Janine needs. A father!

215
00:09:38,452 --> 00:09:41,330
It's just too bad her father isn't here.

216
00:09:42,873 --> 00:09:44,542
[in English] Actually…

217
00:09:47,503 --> 00:09:49,255
I already saw him.

218
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:52,091
[in English] Really? That's good!

219
00:09:52,174 --> 00:09:54,218
At least her parents are complete.

220
00:09:54,302 --> 00:09:55,761
Does Janine know?

221
00:09:57,179 --> 00:09:58,264
Not yet.

222
00:09:59,015 --> 00:10:00,808
We have an agreement…

223
00:10:01,309 --> 00:10:04,020
that I'll introduce
Janine to him tomorrow.

224
00:10:04,103 --> 00:10:07,231
I'm sure she'll be happy
to finally meet her father.

225
00:10:08,691 --> 00:10:09,692
[in English] Who knows?

226
00:10:09,775 --> 00:10:11,193
Maybe your family will be whole again.

227
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:15,573
And the food looks delicious.

228
00:10:15,656 --> 00:10:17,908
I'll start, Auntie. I'm hungry.

229
00:10:22,079 --> 00:10:23,372
All right.

230
00:10:25,082 --> 00:10:26,542
[music fades]

231
00:10:26,626 --> 00:10:28,502
[sighs]

232
00:10:28,586 --> 00:10:29,670
Oh? Atoy!

233
00:10:30,755 --> 00:10:32,256
Looks like you're going somewhere.

234
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:34,050
Uh, what? Do you have a new mission?

235
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:35,635
[Cita] Oh, let's go.

236
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:37,678
Didn't you and Audrey
agree to meet at nine?

237
00:10:37,762 --> 00:10:39,805
The child might be waiting. Let's go.

238
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:41,515
Ah, you're meeting your daughter!

239
00:10:41,599 --> 00:10:43,893
- [quirky music playing]
- Psst, keep quiet, Eme--

240
00:10:43,976 --> 00:10:45,978
Ibyang might hear you.

241
00:10:46,062 --> 00:10:47,772
I haven't told her yet.

242
00:10:47,855 --> 00:10:50,650
Of course, I haven't revealed it yet.
Don't get ahead of me.

243
00:10:51,233 --> 00:10:53,319
Psst, hey. Emerson, huh.

244
00:10:54,362 --> 00:10:56,614
No one should know
what we're talking about.

245
00:10:56,697 --> 00:10:58,157
Do you hear me?

246
00:11:01,911 --> 00:11:03,037
Yes, well…

247
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:03,954
- [titters]
- Huh?

248
00:11:04,038 --> 00:11:04,872
I kind of…

249
00:11:04,955 --> 00:11:06,832
I mentioned it to Tonet.

250
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:08,793
- What?!
- Bu-- But-- But no.

251
00:11:08,876 --> 00:11:11,587
I said it's a secret. A secret!

252
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,255
She can be trusted.

253
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:14,590
It's a secret.

254
00:11:14,673 --> 00:11:16,926
You really can't control your mouth.

255
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:18,010
- Mom, let's go.
- Sorry. No, wait.

256
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:18,928
Wait, I'll come too.

257
00:11:19,011 --> 00:11:19,762
- What?!
- Huh?

258
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:25,101
I'll come too, since I already know
your story.

259
00:11:25,184 --> 00:11:27,770
And I'm really waiting
for the next chapters

260
00:11:27,853 --> 00:11:29,188
in the tele-series of your life!

261
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:31,649
- I'll come with you.
- Whatever! I'll go ahead.

262
00:11:31,732 --> 00:11:33,192
- It's up to you.
- Yes, I'll go ahead.

263
00:11:33,275 --> 00:11:34,485
Come on. You're so slow, Atoy.

264
00:11:34,568 --> 00:11:35,611
Let's go.

265
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:42,535
This could've been a huge mess!

266
00:11:42,618 --> 00:11:44,120
[mysterious music playing]

267
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:46,622
Well, the child is safe.

268
00:11:46,705 --> 00:11:47,998
[in English] No harm, no foul.

269
00:11:49,417 --> 00:11:51,836
Hon, how can you be sure?

270
00:11:51,919 --> 00:11:53,546
What if the child saw something?

271
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:55,881
Or another witness who can link it to you?

272
00:11:57,341 --> 00:11:59,844
No, because if there was,
they would have spoken already.

273
00:11:59,927 --> 00:12:00,970
Okay?

274
00:12:01,053 --> 00:12:02,138
You know, hon.

275
00:12:02,221 --> 00:12:03,848
Janine isn't the lucky one here.

276
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:05,724
[in English] It's you!

277
00:12:05,808 --> 00:12:09,478
If that meddlesome man hadn't come,
she would have been taken.

278
00:12:10,062 --> 00:12:14,525
[in English] We both know that Dad
won't stop until he finds his grandchild.

279
00:12:14,608 --> 00:12:17,862
And he won't forgive you
if he finds out you're behind all this.

280
00:12:17,945 --> 00:12:19,697
[in English] So, you actually
owe that guy a thank you.

281
00:12:21,031 --> 00:12:22,700
What do you want me to do?
Give him a reward?

282
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:25,828
Don't worry. I'll give one,
once I know who he is.

283
00:12:35,296 --> 00:12:36,380
[music fades]

284
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:39,258
Atoy, is this what you'll give Janine?

285
00:12:39,341 --> 00:12:41,510
It's beautiful. She will like it.

286
00:12:41,594 --> 00:12:43,095
- [Emerson sighs]
- [Cita sighs]

287
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:45,723
Wait! What time is it? Maybe…

288
00:12:46,223 --> 00:12:49,477
Looks like mother and child aren't coming.
Maybe they stood you up!

289
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,978
Stop it!

290
00:12:51,061 --> 00:12:53,564
Be sensitive to the situation, huh.

291
00:12:53,647 --> 00:12:57,693
[light music playing]

292
00:12:57,776 --> 00:12:59,695
- [line rings]
- Why isn't Audrey answering?

293
00:12:59,778 --> 00:13:01,113
[phone voice] <i>I'm sorry, all--</i>

294
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:04,700
- [mysterious music playing]
- [deep breath]

295
00:13:04,783 --> 00:13:07,953
- [line rings]
- [sighs]

296
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:10,414
Surely, she has a good reason.

297
00:13:10,998 --> 00:13:12,124
[Emerson] Or maybe

298
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:16,086
she doesn't want to introduce Atoy
as Janine's father anymore.

299
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:18,631
- Haven't I told you to be quiet?
- I'm just stating the obvious.

300
00:13:18,714 --> 00:13:20,466
[Atoy] No, Mom. Emerson is right.

301
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:24,762
Maybe she changed her mind.

302
00:13:26,096 --> 00:13:29,225
Oh, so… what's your plan now?

303
00:13:33,729 --> 00:13:35,231
[music intensifies, concludes]

304
00:13:35,314 --> 00:13:37,566
- Come on, let's get food to go.
- I'm already set here!

305
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:38,984
- Go on, stand up.
- Ah, here, this one.

306
00:13:39,068 --> 00:13:40,569
- We're taking these out.
- Why are you--

307
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:42,071
Let's get this wrapped for take-outs.

308
00:13:42,154 --> 00:13:43,364
[Cita] Where's mine?

309
00:13:43,447 --> 00:13:45,950
[Emerson] Boss, we'll get
this side of the menu to go.

310
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:48,452
[Cita] The sandwich.

311
00:13:48,536 --> 00:13:50,871
[Emerson] Sandwich and spring roll.

312
00:13:50,955 --> 00:13:51,789
[indistinct]

313
00:13:51,872 --> 00:13:54,500
- [suspicious music playing]
- [line ringing]

314
00:13:54,583 --> 00:13:57,336
[indistinct chattering]

315
00:13:57,419 --> 00:13:58,462
[in English] Hello, sir?

316
00:13:58,546 --> 00:14:00,548
Ah, good day.

317
00:14:01,048 --> 00:14:03,634
I just want to ask for intel from you.

318
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:07,346
Hmm.

319
00:14:07,846 --> 00:14:09,306
What do you need?

320
00:14:09,974 --> 00:14:11,892
It's kind of personal, sir.

321
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:15,604
Can you give me the location
of the address of…

322
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:16,522
[clicks tongue]

323
00:14:16,605 --> 00:14:18,148
…the Regalias?

324
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:22,862
[in English] As in Dmitri Regalia?

325
00:14:23,821 --> 00:14:26,198
Why? Is there a problem?

326
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:29,201
His daughter has wronged me. [chuckles]

327
00:14:29,285 --> 00:14:30,619
Audrey.

328
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:31,537
‪[dramatic sting]

329
00:14:36,125 --> 00:14:39,169
Please expedite the papers of my child.

330
00:14:39,253 --> 00:14:41,297
- [music concludes]
- I want us to leave as soon as possible.

331
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:44,383
Yes, ma'am. I'll just update you.

332
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:46,135
[Audrey, in English] Thank you so much.

333
00:14:55,519 --> 00:14:57,313
- Oh, Auntie?
- Gavin.

334
00:14:57,396 --> 00:14:59,064
I thought you and Janine were leaving?

335
00:15:00,816 --> 00:15:03,903
Weren't you going to meet her dad?

336
00:15:04,486 --> 00:15:05,821
[in English] Not anymore.

337
00:15:06,405 --> 00:15:08,240
I changed my mind.

338
00:15:09,617 --> 00:15:11,243
I won't push through with it.

339
00:15:11,952 --> 00:15:12,995
[in English] Why?

340
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:14,580
[pensive music playing]

341
00:15:14,663 --> 00:15:19,752
I've just met my daughter,
and we're still fixing our relationship.

342
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:27,384
If her father is around,
he might lessen our mother-daughter time.

343
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:30,304
And besides…

344
00:15:31,221 --> 00:15:33,766
I don't want Janine to hope
that we'll be whole again.

345
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:37,144
Because I'm sure that won't happen.

346
00:15:37,227 --> 00:15:39,188
[in English] Oh, why not?

347
00:15:39,939 --> 00:15:42,733
That man can never love us.

348
00:15:42,816 --> 00:15:44,777
[music intensifies]

349
00:15:44,860 --> 00:15:46,612
So, I decided…

350
00:15:47,112 --> 00:15:49,323
that my daughter and I
should just move away.

351
00:15:50,532 --> 00:15:53,619
It's better if she doesn't know
about her father.

352
00:15:53,702 --> 00:15:55,579
What did Grandpa say?

353
00:15:56,121 --> 00:15:58,332
Did he agree for you to leave?

354
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,141
[music fades]

355
00:16:16,225 --> 00:16:17,267
[Emerson] Wow, oh.

356
00:16:17,351 --> 00:16:19,228
Their house is huge!

357
00:16:19,311 --> 00:16:21,230
They seem wealthy.

358
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:22,564
[Emerson chuckles]

359
00:16:22,648 --> 00:16:24,149
I'll talk to them.

360
00:16:26,527 --> 00:16:27,820
[doorbell dings]

361
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:31,573
Let me remind you, okay?

362
00:16:31,657 --> 00:16:33,283
Keep your cool.

363
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:35,327
The child might see.

364
00:16:35,411 --> 00:16:38,122
Yes, stay calm! Chill. Stay calm.

365
00:16:38,205 --> 00:16:39,248
[Atoy sighs]

366
00:16:39,331 --> 00:16:43,293
[pensive music playing]

367
00:16:43,377 --> 00:16:44,420
[Atoy scoffs]

368
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:45,796
What do you need?

369
00:16:45,879 --> 00:16:49,883
Uh, is Audrey in there?

370
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:51,552
I need to talk to her.

371
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:55,639
Yes, but no one told me
there was an expected visitor.

372
00:16:56,306 --> 00:16:57,766
Uh, is that so?

373
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:59,476
- Sorry.
- [Atoy] Uh, no.

374
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:02,271
Bro, tell her Atoy is here.

375
00:17:02,771 --> 00:17:05,190
I need to talk to her. It's important.

376
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:06,817
You can't. Sorry.

377
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:08,527
Didn't you hear?

378
00:17:08,610 --> 00:17:10,946
It's important that he talks to her.

379
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,032
Better call your flakey boss!

380
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:13,824
[Cita] Psst.

381
00:17:13,907 --> 00:17:15,409
He said it's not allowed.
You're so insistent.

382
00:17:15,492 --> 00:17:18,495
What does he mean, it's not allowed?
He needs to have a talk with her.

383
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:19,913
You, don't provoke me, huh.

384
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:22,583
We've been waiting three hours, huh.

385
00:17:22,666 --> 00:17:24,043
We still have work.

386
00:17:24,126 --> 00:17:25,294
Call your boss!

387
00:17:25,377 --> 00:17:29,923
[suspicious music playing]

388
00:17:30,007 --> 00:17:33,594
Sir, there's a man outside
insisting to talk to Ma'am Audrey.

389
00:17:36,138 --> 00:17:37,181
Who is that?

390
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:45,731
[tense music playing]

391
00:17:46,315 --> 00:17:49,526
- This guy, saying all sorts of things.
- Emerson.

392
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:50,778
What's your problem, huh?

393
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:51,737
- [Cita] What's wrong with you?!
- [Atoy mutters]

394
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:52,988
- [Atoy mutters]
- Maybe you want…

395
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:54,573
That's enough. I told Atoy to stay calm,

396
00:17:54,656 --> 00:17:55,866
and you're the one fuming!

397
00:17:55,949 --> 00:17:56,909
- Not allow--
- Be quiet!

398
00:17:56,992 --> 00:17:57,910
It's his fault, right?

399
00:17:57,993 --> 00:17:59,286
He's giving this man false hope.

400
00:17:59,369 --> 00:18:00,329
The poor guy.

401
00:18:00,412 --> 00:18:02,372
- Enough.
- What do you want, huh?

402
00:18:02,456 --> 00:18:03,415
Emerson!

403
00:18:04,249 --> 00:18:06,502
- Do you want-- Hmm, oh, my!
- Enough!

404
00:18:06,585 --> 00:18:08,045
- No!
- [Cita mutters]

405
00:18:08,128 --> 00:18:10,380
I'll handle this. I'll talk to them.

406
00:18:12,633 --> 00:18:14,093
Who's causing trouble here?

407
00:18:14,176 --> 00:18:15,469
- Them, sir.
- [Atoy] Enough.

408
00:18:15,552 --> 00:18:17,471
We came all the way here. It's so far.

409
00:18:17,554 --> 00:18:18,722
Mom, hold this.

410
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:24,645
[tense music playing]

411
00:18:24,728 --> 00:18:25,813
You?

412
00:18:28,607 --> 00:18:29,733
- Face me!
- No, sir!

413
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:31,110
[whimpers]

414
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:32,236
[Atoy] No, sir!

415
00:18:32,319 --> 00:18:33,779
[Ame] Sir!

416
00:18:33,862 --> 00:18:34,947
[audience cheering]

417
00:18:35,030 --> 00:18:36,782
Whoo!

418
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:39,326
- My turn.
- Didn't you learn from your parents

419
00:18:39,409 --> 00:18:41,495
to respect your elders?

420
00:18:41,578 --> 00:18:43,455
After I'm done, you'll
really learn something.

421
00:18:44,706 --> 00:18:46,250
He's Atoy.

422
00:18:47,251 --> 00:18:48,127
That's him.

423
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:48,961
[Atoy] <i>Sorry.</i>

424
00:18:49,044 --> 00:18:50,838
I don't talk to drivers.

425
00:18:50,921 --> 00:18:51,797
Bring your boss to me.

426
00:18:52,756 --> 00:18:54,633
You animal, you're making
things hard for us.

427
00:19:00,055 --> 00:19:01,223
[Karla] What's that?

428
00:19:01,306 --> 00:19:04,143
[chuckling]

429
00:19:04,226 --> 00:19:06,061
What are you writing there?

430
00:19:06,145 --> 00:19:07,855
[light music playing]

431
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:09,106
[Tonet] Padua?

432
00:19:09,857 --> 00:19:11,608
Why are you writing it repeatedly?

433
00:19:12,234 --> 00:19:14,111
I'm just practicing.

434
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:20,325
Because this will be my surname
when Tatoy adopts me.

435
00:19:20,409 --> 00:19:21,577
Aw!

436
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:24,705
- You're so good!
- [bright music playing]

437
00:19:24,788 --> 00:19:26,039
So good!

438
00:19:26,123 --> 00:19:28,500
Yes, Ibyang. You're very good.

439
00:19:29,376 --> 00:19:30,669
Thank you!

440
00:19:30,752 --> 00:19:33,046
[chuckles]

441
00:19:34,298 --> 00:19:35,132
Aha!

442
00:19:35,757 --> 00:19:37,801
I'll make a surprise for Tatoy.

443
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:38,719
[chuckles softly]

444
00:19:38,802 --> 00:19:39,761
Don't tell him, okay?

445
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:42,014
[Ame] Mm-hmm. Mmm, okay.

446
00:19:42,097 --> 00:19:43,307
[Ibyang] Please.

447
00:19:43,807 --> 00:19:46,852
[Ibyang inhales]

448
00:19:48,478 --> 00:19:51,273
Ibyang is so happy, right?

449
00:19:52,608 --> 00:19:53,942
Actually, all of us.

450
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:55,319
You're the only one who's sad.

451
00:19:56,403 --> 00:19:57,362
I agree.

452
00:19:57,446 --> 00:19:59,364
- [music concludes]
- Why are you sulking there?

453
00:20:00,365 --> 00:20:03,660
Because Ibyang is so hopeful
she'll be adopted.

454
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:08,373
Well, that's really Atoy's plan.

455
00:20:08,457 --> 00:20:09,416
[Karla] Yes.

456
00:20:10,417 --> 00:20:12,502
Maybe it won't happen.

457
00:20:12,586 --> 00:20:13,629
[Ame] Hmm?

458
00:20:15,380 --> 00:20:16,632
This is just between us, okay?

459
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:19,468
[pensive music playing]

460
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:21,845
Atoy already has a child.

461
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:23,972
What?!

462
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:28,018
[heavy music playing]

463
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:33,899
[music fades]

464
00:20:33,982 --> 00:20:35,067
[in English] Dad.

465
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:45,410
Dad, after what happened to Janine…

466
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:50,332
I want her… to put all that behind her.

467
00:20:51,375 --> 00:20:55,921
If she needs therapy,
we'll just start sessions in the States.

468
00:20:56,505 --> 00:20:58,548
Is that really the only reason?

469
00:20:59,299 --> 00:21:04,888
I know my daughter is still upset with me,
so, I want us to fix things between us.

470
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:07,224
I want her to be close to me.

471
00:21:08,517 --> 00:21:11,520
And I feel like the only way
that it will happen is…

472
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:14,773
when it's just the two of us together.

473
00:21:16,483 --> 00:21:19,861
Audrey, I understand you.

474
00:21:20,487 --> 00:21:23,407
But it's only now that I get to be
with my granddaughter.

475
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:25,242
You'll take her away from me?

476
00:21:28,912 --> 00:21:30,330
[music fades]

477
00:21:30,414 --> 00:21:31,748
What are you doing here?

478
00:21:34,751 --> 00:21:36,420
I need to talk to Audrey.

479
00:21:37,504 --> 00:21:38,797
[smirks]

480
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:40,257
What do you need from my sister?

481
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:42,551
[suspicious music playing]

482
00:21:42,634 --> 00:21:44,136
She's your sister?

483
00:21:47,597 --> 00:21:49,391
I have something important to tell her.

484
00:21:50,809 --> 00:21:51,852
Tell me, instead.

485
00:21:51,935 --> 00:21:53,395
I'll tell her.

486
00:21:54,146 --> 00:21:56,398
You don't know why he's here?

487
00:21:56,481 --> 00:21:57,691
[Atoy] Emerson.

488
00:22:03,196 --> 00:22:04,698
I'm pleading with you.

489
00:22:06,283 --> 00:22:08,035
Let Audrey face me.

490
00:22:08,577 --> 00:22:09,536
[smirks]

491
00:22:09,619 --> 00:22:10,871
You're out of your mind.

492
00:22:11,580 --> 00:22:12,873
Why would I do that?

493
00:22:14,041 --> 00:22:15,751
You better leave.

494
00:22:17,961 --> 00:22:20,422
I won't leave until I talk to her.

495
00:22:24,343 --> 00:22:25,510
Is that so?

496
00:22:26,344 --> 00:22:27,512
[sniffs]

497
00:22:27,596 --> 00:22:28,555
[music fades]

498
00:22:29,222 --> 00:22:30,140
[Cita] Hey!

499
00:22:30,223 --> 00:22:33,185
[rock music playing]

500
00:22:45,781 --> 00:22:47,741
They already said you should leave.

501
00:22:47,824 --> 00:22:49,284
Ah, here we go, here we go.
We're leaving now.

502
00:22:49,367 --> 00:22:50,452
You can't take a joke!

503
00:22:51,119 --> 00:22:52,746
Atoy, let's go. Auntie.

504
00:22:53,622 --> 00:22:56,458
- [Cita] Emerson.
- I just need to talk to your sister.

505
00:22:57,250 --> 00:22:58,502
[tense music playing]

506
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:00,212
Should I just finish you off?

507
00:23:00,295 --> 00:23:02,005
- [Emerson] No, don't do that.
- [Red] Huh?

508
00:23:03,298 --> 00:23:05,550
[Emerson] Atoy, Atoy!

509
00:23:07,302 --> 00:23:09,054
[Cita and Emerson] Hey!

510
00:23:09,137 --> 00:23:12,099
[grunting]

511
00:23:12,182 --> 00:23:13,433
[Cita squeals]

512
00:23:14,601 --> 00:23:15,977
[Cita] Atoy!

513
00:23:18,271 --> 00:23:19,231
Grandpa! Auntie!

514
00:23:19,314 --> 00:23:20,857
Dad is fighting with someone outside!

515
00:23:21,858 --> 00:23:23,026
[in English] Stay here.

516
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:24,611
Stay here.

517
00:23:24,694 --> 00:23:28,907
[tense music playing]

518
00:23:29,491 --> 00:23:31,118
[Dmitri] What is happening here?

519
00:23:33,787 --> 00:23:34,788
Brother Atoy?

520
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:37,290
[music fades]

521
00:23:37,374 --> 00:23:38,375
[in English] Wait.

522
00:23:39,084 --> 00:23:39,918
[Dmitri, in English] I know you.

523
00:23:41,128 --> 00:23:42,546
[in English] You're the Master Cutter.

524
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:44,214
[heavy music playing]

525
00:23:44,297 --> 00:23:45,799
That's you?

526
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:48,301
What are you doing here?

527
00:23:48,885 --> 00:23:50,303
Is there a problem?

528
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:54,099
Why don't you ask your daughter?

529
00:23:54,683 --> 00:23:56,268
[in English] Atoy, not now!

530
00:23:56,977 --> 00:23:58,645
Let's talk in private.

531
00:23:59,813 --> 00:24:01,148
Why is that?

532
00:24:01,231 --> 00:24:03,150
You don't know how to keep your word.

533
00:24:03,233 --> 00:24:04,860
You made me wait!

534
00:24:04,943 --> 00:24:05,986
What?

535
00:24:06,069 --> 00:24:08,196
You want to deprive me of my child?

536
00:24:08,280 --> 00:24:09,406
[music fades]

537
00:24:09,489 --> 00:24:10,574
What child are you talking about?

538
00:24:10,657 --> 00:24:12,242
[tense music playing]

539
00:24:12,325 --> 00:24:13,618
What is he saying about your child?

540
00:24:16,496 --> 00:24:21,918
[music swells]

541
00:24:24,754 --> 00:24:30,719
[electronic blipping]

542
00:24:35,223 --> 00:24:36,266
Why are there squatters here?

543
00:24:36,349 --> 00:24:38,643
Aren't you afraid they might rob you?

544
00:24:38,727 --> 00:24:41,897
Do you want to come out of here
with only your eyes unbruised?

545
00:24:41,980 --> 00:24:44,774
Do you want our child to grow up
without knowing a father?

546
00:24:44,858 --> 00:24:47,485
- You're my daddy?
- Yes, my dear.

547
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:48,820
I don't like you!

548
00:24:48,904 --> 00:24:50,197
Janine--

549
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:51,156
[Audrey] I'll just have a talk with her.

550
00:24:51,239 --> 00:24:53,241
What if Tatoy already has a child?

551
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:54,409
Well, in that case…

552
00:24:54,492 --> 00:24:55,368
UP NEXT

553
00:24:55,452 --> 00:24:56,786
I will have a sibling!

554
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:57,829
[Karla] What if you don't like her?

555
00:24:58,455 --> 00:24:59,581
If she's not nice?

556
00:24:59,664 --> 00:25:01,708
You're just claiming him as your dad.

557
00:25:03,001 --> 00:25:04,794
I am his real daughter.

558
00:25:04,878 --> 00:25:06,755
You're just a foster child, Ibyang!

559
00:25:06,838 --> 00:25:08,673
- [Janine] Right, Daddy?
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

560
00:25:08,757 --> 00:25:11,051
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

561
00:25:11,134 --> 00:25:14,179
♪ <i>One cut and it's settled</i> ♪

562
00:25:14,262 --> 00:25:16,139
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
